Casa Yari is an amazing gem in Logan square right off of Fullerton.  They have a newly created back patio area with 100% shade made with those pop up tents.  The staff is very knowledgeable about not just the dishes served but the history and location they originat from.  Omg th Empanadas here are some of the best.  And you get 3 giant ones per order.   The croquettes were also very nice and had a good cheezy flavor to them.  A must try also.  Hands down some amazing authentic Latin food dine right.    Spiced down a bit but fabulous none the less.  Give this place a try you will love it!!

The food was very good. Although I have a few issues with it. First the service was so mediocre! The waitress attitude was as if she didn’t want to be there and wanted everyone to know it! She took forever to bring water, Then the  drinks! The food took a long time as well. I had the chuleton, the chuletas where fried to perfection yet no seasoning. The mofongo de yuca was amazing! My friends seem to love their mofongo Del Mar and jibaritos.  I couldn’t try it because I’m allergic. The place was super clean and looked great! The parcha juice was unbelievably good tasted like I was back in Puerto Rico. The rice was very good yet old! I’m Puerto Rican and Cocinero myself and you can’t tell me that rice was fresh. Still tasted good but still old. Overall I would definitely come back if we get that friendly service everyone speaks off and they season the chuletas lol.

You hear "Puerto Rico" and an array of foods come to mind: tostones, mofongo, and Arroz con Gandules. But that picture doesn't tell the whole story, especially not in the kitchen of Casa Yari. In the preparation of the ingredients used for each dish, she brings the flavor forward without distraction. She obtains clarity in taste and presentation so that the guest can fully realize the essence of the vegan products used.  Her intention becomes exceptionally clear in the creation of delicious meat-free dishes, which are available on the menu vegetarian (or vegan).  Casa Yari's vegan dishes aren't bland; on the contrary, they're colorful, exciting and complex.  Yari Vargas chef at Casa Yari definitely knows how to incorporate jackfruit and seitan into her Puerto Rican cooking.

Finally, my restaurant curse has ended! After sitting through countless disappointing meals to the point where I started developing a complex - we dined here.  We ordered the paladar, croquetas de yuca and nidos de camarons to start. Since we shared it with a large group, I was only able to get a small bite of each, but everything was well presented and explained by Hector, our waiter.  He was wonderful, and everything we ordered was amazing, flavorful, well made and delicious.  For the main I ordered Trifongo - fabulous, well presented - I savored every bite.  Finally! I'm so excited, I can't wait to go back and try the jibaritos.

4/21/18 we stopped by for a late lunch, nearly 4pm. Service was polite and attentive and willing to take questions and small substitutions,  to accommodate a dietary need. I had the Caribbean nachos, chicken and tropical salsa on fried plantains, (not regular nachos..) my friend had the pastelon,  because she loves it and she said not many places make it, she complimented the chef, she said she had not had beans with that flavor since her mother used to make them. We finished with the Bread pudding with coconut ice cream. The food is made fresh, therefore takes the correct amount of time to cook but not overlong, to keep us busy they brought some complimentary home made chips with caribbean sauce to the table and a sprinkle of parmesan cheese. The chef/owner is highly trained and talented, everything was delicious, and served  as if it were a 5 star restaurant. We finished with the Bread pudding, putting that order in at the same time as the nachos because it takes 15 mins to cook. Again, delicious. Pricing was very reasonable for the quality of service and food. Having worked in restaurants, and cooking everything fresh, I don't know how well they handle an absolute rush, but this is a BYOB restaurant, so plan ahead and take advantage of this place in the afternoons, when the service, music, ambiance lets you really enjoy your meal and company.

Not ever going back. Maybe it was an off day but if flan is what you're known for then there should never be an off day. Sucks I really wanted to love it.
